item.title: U.S., China Jockey for Position in Pacific With Moves on Security, Trade
item.description: The U.S. has been amassing a network of alliances, and its latest effort with the U.K. aims to provide Australia with nuclear submarines to strengthen deterrence in the Indo-Pacific region. For its part, China said it would apply to join a regional economic pact.

item.title: France Says It Has Killed Islamic State Leader
item.description: Adnan Abu Walid al-Sahrawi led an operation that killed four U.S. servicemen in Niger in 2017 and was the architect of one of the terrorist outfit’s most successful franchises.

item.title: Facebook Employees Flag Drug Cartels and Human Traffickers. The Company's Response Is Weak, Documents Show.
item.description: Employees raised alarms about how the site is used in developing countries, where its user base is already huge and expanding. In many instances Facebook’s response is inadequate or nothing at all.

item.title: Italy to Impose Strict Covid-19 Health Pass for All Workers
item.description: The country is making Covid-19 health passes mandatory for all workers in the private and public sectors, in one of the toughest vaccine-promoting measures adopted by any major Western country.

item.title: Without Angela Merkel, Germany's Conservatives Face Possible Election Rout
item.description: A gaffe-prone new candidate, voter fatigue and the popular chancellor’s almost complete absence from the campaign could converge to deliver the conservative bloc’s worst national result ever, according to pollsters and analysts.

item.title: Many in Rural Afghanistan Welcome an Unfamiliar Peace
item.description: While Taliban rule prompted an exodus from Kabul, many people in villages ravaged by war express relief that the killings and destruction have finally stopped.
